obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (14372)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14372&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Securities Contracts`
  line `(Regulation) Act, 1956.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 20th February, 1957, vide Notification No. S.R.O. 528, dated 16th February, 1957, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (14373)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14373&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) Contract means a contract for or relating to the purchase or sale of securities;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) corporatisation means the succession of a recognised stock exchange, being a body of`
  line `individuals or a society registered under the Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860), by another`
  line `stock exchange, being a company incorporated for the purpose of assisting, regulating or controlling`
  line `the business of buying, selling or dealing in securities carried on by such individuals or society;`
  line
  line `(ab) demutualisation means the segregation of ownership and management from the trading`
  line `rights of the members of a recognised stock exchange in accordance with a scheme approved by the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India;]`
  line
  line ^2[
  line `^3[(ac)] derivative includes--`
  line
  line `(A) a security derived from a debt instrument, share, loan, whether secured or unsecured, risk`
  line `instrument or contract for differences or any other form of security;`
  line
  line `(B) a contact which derives its value from the prices, or index of prices, of underlying`
  line securities;]
  line
  line `^4[(C) commodity derivatives; and`
  line
  line `(D) such other instruments as may be declared by the Central Government to be derivatives;]`
  line
  line `(b) Government security means a security created and issued, whether before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act, by the Central Government or a State Government for the purpose of`
  line `raising a public loan and having one of the forms specified in clause (2) of section 2 of the Public`
  line `Debt Act, 1944 (13 of 1944);`
  line
  line `^4[(bb) goods mean every kind of movable property other than actionable claims, money and`
  line securities;
  line
  line `(bc) commodity derivative means a contract--`
  line
  line `(i) for the delivery of such goods, as may be notified by the Central Government in the`
  line `Official Gazette, and which is not a ready delivery contract; or`
  line
  line `(ii) for differences, which derives its value from prices or indices of prices of such underlying`
  line `goods or activities, services, rights, interests and events, as may be notified by the Central`
  line `Government, in consultation with the Board, but does not include securities as referred to in`
  line `sub-clauses (A) and (B) of clause (ac);]`
  line
  line `(c) member means a member of a recognised stock exchange;`
  line
  line `^4[(ca) non-transferable specific delivery contract means a specific delivery contract, the rights`
  line `or liabilities under which or under any delivery order, railway receipt, bill of lading, warehouse`
  line `receipt or any other documents of title relating thereto are not transferable;]`
  line
  line `(d) option in securities means a contract for the purchase or sale of a right to buy or sell, or a`
  line `right to buy and sell, securities in future, and includes a teji, a mandi, a teji mandi, a galli, a put, a call`
  line `or a put and call in securities;`
  line
  line `^5i9560(da) pooled investment vehicle means a fund established in India in the form of a trust or otherwise, such as mutual fund, alternative investment fund, collective investment scheme or a business trust as defined in sub-section (13A) of section 2 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and registered with the Securities and Exchange Board of India, or such other fund, which raises or collects monies from investors and invests such funds in accordance with such regulations as may be made by the Securities and Exchange Board of India in this behalf;]`
  line
  line `(e) prescribed means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `^4[(ea) ready delivery contract means a contract which provides for the delivery of goods and`
  line `the payment of a price therefor, either immediately, or within such period not exceeding eleven days`
  line `after the date of the contract and subject to such conditions as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify in respect of any goods, the period under such contract not`
  line `being capable of extension by the mutual consent of the parties thereto or otherwise:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such contract is performed either wholly or in part;`
  line
  line `(I) by realisation of any sum of money being the difference between the contract rate and the`
  line `settlement rate or clearing rate or the rate of any offsetting contract; or`
  line
  line `(II) by any other means whatsoever, and as a result of which the actual tendering of the goods`
  line `covered by the contract or payment of the full price therefor is dispensed with, then such contract`
  line `shall not be deemed to be a ready delivery contract;]`
  line
  line `(f) recognised stock exchange means a stock exchange which is for the time being recognised`
  line `by the Central Government under section 4;`
  line
  line `(g) rules, with reference to the rules relating in general to the constitution and management of a`
  line `stock exchange, includes, in the case of a stock exchange which is an incorporated association, its`
  line `memorandum and articles of association;`
  line
  line `^6[(ga) scheme means a scheme for corporatisation or demutualisation of a recognised stock`
  line `exchange which may provide for--`
  line
  line `(i) the issue of shares for a lawful consideration and provision of trading rights in lieu of`
  line `membership cards of members of a recognised stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(ii) the restrictions on voting rights;`
  line
  line `(iii) the transfer of property, business, assets, rights, liabilities, recognitions, contracts of the`
  line `recognised stock exchange, legal proceedings by, or against, the recognised stock exchange,`
  line `whether in the name of the recognised stock exchange or any trustee or otherwise and any`
  line `permission given to, or by, the recognised stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(iv) the transfer of employees of a recognised stock exchange to another recognised stock`
  line exchange;
  line
  line `(v) any other matter required for the purpose of, or in connection with, the corporatisation or`
  line `demutulisation, as the case may be, of the recognised stock exchange;]`
  line
  line ^7[
  line `^8[(gb)] Securities Appellate Tribunal means a Securities Appellate Tribunal established under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 15K of the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992);]`
  line
  line `(h) securities include--`
  line
  line `(i) shares, scrips stocks, bonds, debentures, debenture stock or other marketable securities of`
  line `a like nature in or of any incorporated company or ^9[ or a pooled investment vehicle or other body corporate];`
  line
  line `^10[(ia) derivative;`
  line
  line `(ib) units or any other instrument issued by any collective investment scheme to the investors`
  line `in such schemes;]`
  line
  line `^11[(ic) security receipt as defined in clause (zg) of section 2 of the Securitisation and`
  line `Reconstruction of Financial Assets and Enforcement of Security Interest Act, 2002 (54 of 2002);]`
  line
  line `^12[(id) units or any other such instrument issued to the investors under any mutual fund`
  line scheme;]
  line
  line `^13[(ida) units or any other instrument issued by any pooled investment vehicle;]br`
  line
  line `^14[Explanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that securities shall not`
  line `include any unit linked insurance policy or scrips or any such instrument or unit, by whatever`
  line `name called, which provides a combined benefit risk on the life of the persons and investment by`
  line `such persons and issued by an insurer referred to in clause (9) of section 2 of the Insurance Act,`
  line `1938 (4 of 1938).]`
  line
  line `^15[(ie) any certificate or instrument (by whatever name called), issued to an investor by any`
  line `issuer being a special purpose distinct entity which possesses any debt or receivable, including`
  line `mortgage debt, assigned to such entity, and acknowledging beneficial interest of such investor in`
  line `such debt or receiveable including mortgage debt, as the case may be;]`
  line
  line `(ii) Government securities; and`
  line
  line `(iii) rights or interests in securities;`
  line
  line `^16[(ha) specific delivery contract means a commodity derivative which provides for the`
  line `actual delivery of specific qualities or types of goods during a specified future period at a`
  line `price fixed thereby or to be fixed in the manner thereby agreed and in which the names of`
  line `both the buyer and the seller are mentioned;]`
  line
  line `^17[(i) spot delivery contract means a contract which provides for,--`
  line
  line `(a) actual delivery of securities and the payment of a price therefor either on the same day as`
  line `the date of the contract or on the next day, the actual period taken for the dispatch of the securities`
  line `or the remittance of money therefor through the post being excluded from the computation of the`
  line `period aforesaid if the parties to the contract do not reside in the same town or locality;`
  line
  line `(b) transfer of the securities by the depository from the account of a beneficial owner to the`
  line `account of another beneficial owner when such securities are dealt with by a depository;]`
  line
  line `^18[(j) stock exchange means--`
  line
  line `(a) any body of individuals, whether incorporated or not, constituted before corporatisation`
  line `and demutualisation under sections 4A and 4B, or`
  line
  line `(b) a body corporate incorporated under the Companies Act, 1956 whether under a scheme of`
  line `corporatisation and demutualisation or otherwise,`
  line
  line `for the purpose of assisting, regulating or controlling the business of buying, selling or dealing in`
  line securities;]
  line
  line `^19[(k) transferable specific delivery contract means a specific delivery contract which is not a`
  line `non-transferable specific delivery contract and which is subject to such conditions relating to its`
  line `transferability as the Central Government may by notification in the Official Gazette, specify in this`
  line behalf.]
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (aa) re-lettered as clause (ac) thereof by Act 1 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 133 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 148 (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 32 of 1999, s. 2 (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  line
  line `8. Clause (ga) re-lettered as clause (gb) thereof by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f.12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 148, for other body corporate (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 54 of 2002, s. 41 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 21-6-2002).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-10-2005).`
  line
  line `13. Ins by Act 13 of 2021, s. 148 (w.e.f.1-4-2021).`
  line
  line `14. The Explanation ins. by Act 26 of 2010, s. 4 (w.e.f. 9-4-2010).`
  line
  line `15. Ins. by Act 27 of 2007, s. 2 (w.e.f. 28-5-2007).`
  line
  line `16. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 133 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
  line
  line `17. Subs. by Act 22 of 1996, s. 30 and the Schedule, for clause (i) (w.e.f. 20-9-1995).`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 2, for clause (j) (w.e.f. 12-10-2005).`
  line
  line `19. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 133 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (14374)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Interpretation of certain words and expressions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 32 of 1999, s. 3 (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14374&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[2A. Interpretation of certain words and expressions.--Words and expressions used herein and`
  line `not defined in this Act but defined in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) or the Securities and Exchange`
  line `Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) or the Depositories Act, 1996 (22 of 1996) shall have the same`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in those Acts.]`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (14375)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Application for recognition of stock exchanges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14375&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any stock exchange, which is desirous of`
  line `being recognised for the purposes of this Act, may make an application in the prescribed manner to the`
  line `Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every application under sub-section (1) shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed, and`
  line `shall be accompanied by a copy of the bye-laws of the stock exchange for the regulation and control of`
  line `contracts and also a copy of the rules relating in general to the constitution of the stock exchange, and in`
  line `particular, to--`
  line
  line `(a) the governing body of such stock exchange, its constitution and powers of management and`
  line `the manner in which its business is to be transacted;`
  line
  line `(b) the powers and duties of the office bearers of the stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(c) the admission into the stock exchange of various classes of members, the qualifications for`
  line `membership, and the exclusion, suspension, expulsion and re-admission of members therefrom or`
  line thereinto;
  line
  line `(d) the procedure for the registration of partnerships as members of the stock exchange in cases`
  line `where the rules provide for such membership; and the nomination and appointment of authorised`
  line `representatives and clerks.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (14376)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Grant of recognition to stock exchanges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14376&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is satisfied, after`
  line `making such inquiry as may be necessary in this behalf and after obtaining such further information, if`
  line `any, as it may require,--`
  line
  line `(a) that the rules and bye-laws of a stock exchange applying for registration are in conformity`
  line `with such conditions as may be prescribed with a view to ensure fair dealing and to protect investors;`
  line
  line `(b) that the stock exchange is willing to comply with any other conditions (including conditions`
  line `as to the number of members) which the Central Government, after consultation with the governing`
  line `body of the stock exchange and having regard to the area served by the stock exchange and its`
  line `standing and the nature of the securities dealt with by it, may impose for the purpose of carrying out`
  line `the objects of this Act; and`
  line
  line `(c) that it would be in the interest of the trade and also in the public interest to grant recognition to`
  line `the stock exchange;`
  line
  line `it may grant recognition to the stock exchange subject to the conditions imposed upon it as aforesaid and`
  line `in such form as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The conditions which the Central Government may prescribe under clause (a) of sub-section (1)`
  line `for the grant of recognition to the stock exchanges may include, among other matters, conditions relating`
  line to,--
  line
  line `(i) the qualifications for membership of stock exchanges;`
  line
  line `(ii) the manner in which contracts shall be entered into and enforced as between members;`
  line
  line `(iii) the representation of the Central Government on each of the stock exchanges by such number`
  line `of persons not exceeding three as the Central Government may nominate in this behalf; and`
  line
  line `(iv) the maintenance of accounts of members and their audit by Chartered accountants wherever`
  line `such audit is required by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every grant of recognition to a stock exchange under this section shall be published in the Gazette`
  line `of India and also in the Official Gazette of the State in which the principal office of the stock exchange is`
  line `situate, and such recognition shall have effect as from the date of its publication in the Gazette of India.`
  line
  line `(4) No application for the grant of recognition shall be refused except after giving an opportunity to`
  line `the stock exchange concerned to be heard in the matter; and the reasons for such refusal shall be`
  line `communicated to the stock exchange in writing.`
  line
  line `(5) No rules of a recognised stock exchange relating to any of the matters specified in sub-section (2)`
  line `of section 3 shall be amended except with the approval of the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (14377)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 6
  title `Corporatisation and demutualisation of stock exchanges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14377&sectionno=4A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[4A. Corporatisation and demutualisation of stock exchanges.--On and from the appointed date,`
  line `all recognised stock exchanges (if not corporatised and demutualised before the appointed date) shall be`
  line `corporatised and demutualised in accordance with the provisions contained in section 4B:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Securities and Exchange Board of India may, if it is satisfied that any recognised`
  line `stock exchange was prevented by sufficient cause from being corporatised and demutualised on or after`
  line `the appointed date, specify another appointed date in respect of that recognised stock exchange and such`
  line `recognised stock exchange may continue as such before such appointed date.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "appointed date" means the date which the Securities`
  line `and Exchange Board of India may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint and different appointed`
  line `dates may be appointed for different recognised stock exchanges.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_b:
  sectionId (14378)
  sectionNo 4B
  orderNo 7
  title `Procedure for corporatisation and demutualisation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 3 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14378&sectionno=4B&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_4_b_content:
  string
  line `^14B. Procedure for corporatisation and demutualisation.--(1) All recognised stock exchanges`
  line `referred to in section 4A shall, within such time as may be specified by the Securities and Exchange`
  line `Board of India, submit a scheme for corporatisation and demutualisation for its approval:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Securities and Exchange Board of India, may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, specify name of the recognised stock exchange, which had already been corporatised and`
  line `demutualised, and such stock exchange shall not be required to submit the scheme under this section.`
  line
  line `(2) On receipt of the scheme referred to in sub-section (1), the Securities and Exchange Board of`
  line `India may, after making such enquiry as may be necessary in this behalf and obtaining such further`
  line `information, if any, as it may require and if it is satisfied that it would be in the interest of the trade and`
  line `also in the public interest, approve the scheme with or without modification.`
  line
  line `(3) No scheme under sub-section (2) shall be approved by the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `if the issue of shares for a lawful consideration or provision of trading rights in lieu of membership card`
  line `of the members of a recognised stock exchange or payment of dividends to members have been proposed`
  line `out of any reserves or assets of that stock exchange.`
  line
  line `(4) Where the scheme is approved under sub-section (2), the scheme so approved shall be published`
  line `immediately by--`
  line
  line `(a) the Securities and Exchange Board of India in the Official Gazette;`
  line
  line `(b) the recognised stock exchange in such two daily newspapers circulating in India, as may be`
  line `specified by the Securities and Exchange Board of India,`
  line
  line `and upon such publication, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in this Act or any other`
  line `law for the time being in force or any agreement, award, judgment, decree or other instrument for the time`
  line `being in force, the scheme shall have effect and be binding on all persons and authorities including all members, creditors, depositors and employees of the recognised stock exchange and on all persons having`
  line `any contract, right, power, obligation or liability with, against, over, to, or in connection with, the`
  line `recognised stock exchange or its members.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the Securities and Exchange Board of India is satisfied that it would not be in the interest`
  line `of the trade and also in the public interest to approve the scheme under sub-section (2), it may, by an`
  line `order, reject the scheme and such order of rejection shall be published by it in the Official Gazette:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Securities and Exchange Board of India shall give a reasonable opportunity of being`
  line `heard to all the persons concerned and the recognised stock exchange concerned before passing an order`
  line `rejecting the scheme.`
  line
  line `(6) The Securities and Exchange Board of India may, while approving the scheme under`
  line `sub-section (2), by an order in writing, restrict--`
  line
  line `(a) the voting rights of the shareholders who are also stock brokers of the recognised stock`
  line exchange;
  line
  line `(b) the right of shareholders or a stock broker of the recognised stock exchange to appoint the`
  line `representatives on the governing board of the stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(c) the maximum number of representatives of the stock brokers of the recognised stock exchange`
  line `to be appointed on the governing board of the recognised stock exchange, which shall not exceed onefourth`
  line `of the total strength of the governing board.`
  line
  line `(7) The order made under sub-section (6) shall be published in the Official Gazette and on the`
  line `publication thereof, the order shall, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Companies`
  line `Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or any other law for the time being in force, have full effect.`
  line
  line `(8) Every recognised stock exchange, in respect of which the scheme for corporatisation or`
  line `demutualisation has been approved under sub-section (2), shall, either by fresh issue of equity share to the`
  line `public or in any other manner as may be specified by the regulations made by the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India, ensure that at least fifty-one per cent. of its equity share capital is held, within`
  line `twelve months from the date of publication of the order under sub-section (7), by the public other than`
  line `shareholders having trading rights:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Securities and Exchange Board of India may, on sufficient cause being shown to it`
  line `and in the public interest, extend the said period by another twelve months.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (14379)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 8
  title `Withdrawal of recognition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14379&sectionno=5&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] If the Central Government is of opinion that the recognition`
  line `granted to a stock exchange under the provisions of this Act should, in the interest of the trade or in the`
  line `public interest, be withdrawn, the Central Government may serve on the governing body of the stock`
  line `exchange a written notice that the Central Government is considering the withdrawal of the recognition`
  line `for the reasons stated in the notice, and after giving an opportunity to the governing body to be heard in`
  line `the matter, the Central Government may withdraw, by notification in the Official Gazette, the recognition`
  line `granted to the stock exchange:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such withdrawal shall affect the validity of any contract entered into or made before`
  line `the date of the notification, and the Central Government may, after consultation with the stock exchange,`
  line `make such provision as it deems fit in the notification of withdrawal or in any subsequent notification`
  line `similarly published for the due performance of any contracts outstanding on that date.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Where the recognised stock exchange has not been corporatised or demutualised or it fails to`
  line `submit the scheme referred to in sub-section (1) of section 4B within the specified time therefor or the`
  line `scheme has been rejected by the Securities and Exchange Board of India under sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 4B, the recognition granted to such stock exchange under section 4, shall, notwithstanding`
  line `anything to the contrary contained in this Act, stand withdrawn and the Central Government shall publish,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, such withdrawal of recognition:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such withdrawal shall affect the validity of any contract entered into or made before`
  line `the date of the notification, and the Securities and Exchange Board of India may, after consultation with`
  line `the stock exchange, make such provisions as it deems fit in the order rejecting the scheme published in`
  line `the Official Gazette under sub-section (5) of section 4B.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 5 numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 1 of 2005, s. 4 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (14380)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power of Central Government to call for periodical returns or direct inquiries to be made.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14380&sectionno=6&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every recognised stock exchange shall furnish to the ^1[Securities and Exchange Board of`
  line `India] such periodical returns relating to its affairs as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) Every recognised stock exchange and every member thereof shall maintain and preserve for such`
  line `periods not exceeding five years such books of account, and other documents as the Central Government,`
  line `after consultation with the stock exchange concerned, may prescribe in the interest of the trade or in the`
  line `public interest, and such books of account, and other documents shall be subject to inspection at all`
  line `reasonable times ^2[by the Securities and Exchange Board of India].`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-sections (1) and (2), the ^1[Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India], if it is satisfied that it is in the interest of the trade or in the public interest so to`
  line `do, may, by order in writing,--`
  line
  line `(a) call upon a recognised stock exchange or any member thereof to furnish in writing such`
  line `information or explanation relating to the affairs of the stock exchange or of the member in relation to`
  line `the stock exchange as the ^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India] may require; or`
  line
  line `(b) appoint one or more persons to make an inquiry in the prescribed manner in relation to the`
  line `affairs of the governing body of a stock exchange or the affairs of any of the members of the stock`
  line `exchange in relation to the stock exchange and submit a report of the result of such inquiry to the`
  line `^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India] within such time as may be specified in the order or, in the`
  line `case of an inquiry in relation to the affairs of any of the members of a stock exchange, direct the`
  line `governing body to make the inquiry and submit its report to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an inquiry in relation to the affairs of a recognised stock exchange or the affairs of any of`
  line `its members in relation to the stock exchange has been undertaken under sub-section (3),--`
  line
  line `(a) every director, manager, secretary or other officer of such stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(b) every member of such stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(c) if the member of the stock exchange is a firm, every partner, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the firm; and`
  line
  line `(d) every other person or body of persons who has had dealings in the course of business with any`
  line `of the persons mentioned in clauses (a), (b) and (c), whether directly or indirectly;`
  line
  line `shall be bound to produce before the authority making the inquiry all such books of account, and other`
  line `documents in his custody or power relating to or having a bearing on the subject-matter of such inquiry`
  line `and also to furnish the authorities within such time as may be specified with any such statement or`
  line `information relating thereto as may be required of him.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1992, s. 33 and the Schedule, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 30-1-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 33 and the Schedule, ibid., for "by the Central Government" (w.e.f. 30-1-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (14381)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 10
  title `Annual reports to be furnished to the Central Government by stock exchanges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14381&sectionno=7&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `recognised stock exchange shall furnish the Central Government with a copy of the annual report, and`
  line `such annual report shall contain such particulars as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (14382)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 11
  title `Power of recognised stock exchange to make rules restricting voting rights, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 49 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-12-1959).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14382&sectionno=7A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Power of recognised stock exchange to make rules restricting voting rights, etc.--(1) A`
  line `recognised stock exchange may make rules or amend any rules made by it to provide for all or any of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the restriction of voting rights to members only in respect of any matter placed before the`
  line `stock exchange at any meeting;`
  line
  line `(b) the regulation of voting rights in respect of any matter placed before the stock exchange at any`
  line `meeting so that each member may be entitled to have one vote only, irrespective of his share of the`
  line `paid-up equity capital of the stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(c) the restriction on the right of a member to appoint another person as his proxy to attend and`
  line `vote at a meeting of the stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(d) such incidental, consequential and supplementary matters as may be necessary to give effect`
  line `to any of the matters specified in clauses (a), (b) and (c).`
  line
  line `(2) No rules of a recognised stock exchange made or amended in relation to any matter referred to in`
  line `clauses (a) to (d) of sub-section (1) shall have effect until they have been approved by the Central`
  line `Government and published by that Government in the Official Gazette and, in approving the rules so`
  line `made or amended, the Central Government may make such modifications therein as it thinks fit, and on`
  line `such publication, the rules as approved by the Central Government shall be deemed to have been validly`
  line `made, notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956).]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (14383)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Central Government to direct rules to be made or to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 19, for "six months" (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14383&sectionno=8&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, after`
  line `consultation with the governing bodies of stock exchanges generally or with the governing body of any`
  line `stock exchange in particular, the Central Government is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to`
  line `do, it may, by order in writing together with a statement of the reasons therefor, direct recognised stock`
  line `exchanges generally or any recognised stock exchange in particular, as the case may be, to make any rules`
  line `or to amend any rules already made in respect of all or any of the matters specified in sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 3 within a period of ^1[two months] from the date of the order .`
  line
  line `(2) If any recognised stock exchange fails or neglects to comply with any order made under`
  line `sub-section (1) within the period specified therein, the Central Government may make the rules for, or`
  line `amend the rules made by, the recognised stock exchange, either in the form proposed in the order or with`
  line `such modifications thereof as may be agreed to between the stock exchange and the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Where in pursuance of this section any rules have been made or amended, the rules so made or`
  line `amended shall be published in the Gazette of India and also in the Official Gazette or Gazettes of the`
  line `State or States in which the principal office or offices of the recognised stock exchange or exchanges is or`
  line `are situate, and, on the publication thereof in the Gazette of India, the rules so made or amended shall,`
  line `notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), or in any`
  line `other law for the time being in force, have effect, as if they had been made or amended by the recognised`
  line `stock exchange or stock exchanges, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (14384)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 13
  title `Clearing corporation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 5 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14384&sectionno=8A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Clearing corporation.--(1) A recognised stock exchange may, with the prior approval of the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India, transfer the duties and functions of a clearing house to a clearing`
  line `corporation, being a company incorporated under the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), for the purpose`
  line of--
  line
  line `(a) the periodical settlement of contracts and differences thereunder;`
  line
  line `(b) the delivery of, and payment for, securities;`
  line
  line `(c) any other matter incidental to, or connected with, such transfer.`
  line
  line `(2) Every clearing corporation shall, for the purpose of transfer of the duties and functions of a`
  line `clearing house to a clearing corporation referred to in sub-section (1), make bye-laws and submit the same`
  line `to the Securities and Exchange Board of India for its approval.`
  line
  line `(3) The Securities and Exchange Board of India may, on being satisfied that it is in the interest of the`
  line `trade and also in the public interest to transfer the duties and functions of a clearing house to a clearing`
  line `corporation, grant approval to the bye-laws submitted to it under sub-section (2) and approve the transfer`
  line `of the duties and functions of a clearing house to a clearing corporation referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(4) The provisions of sections 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11 and 12 shall, as far as may be, apply to a clearing`
  line `corporation referred to in sub-section (1) as they apply in relation to a recognised stock exchange.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (14385)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power of recognised stock exchanges to make bye-laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1992, s. 33 and the Schedule, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 30-1-1992).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14385&sectionno=9&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any recognised stock exchange`
  line `may, subject to the previous approval of the ^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India], make bye-laws`
  line `for the regulation and control of contracts.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such bye-laws may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the opening and closing of markets and the regulation of the hours of trade;`
  line
  line `(b) a clearing house for the periodical settlement of contracts and differences there under, the`
  line `delivery of and payment for securities, the passing on of delivery orders and the regulation and`
  line `maintenance of such clearing house;`
  line
  line `(c) the submission to the ^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India] by the clearing house as soon`
  line `as may be after each periodical settlement of all or any of the following particulars as the ^1[Securities`
  line `and Exchange Board of India] may, from time to time, require, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) the total number of each category of security carried over from one settlement period to`
  line another;
  line
  line `(ii) the total number of each category of security, contracts in respect of which have been`
  line `squared up during the course of each settlement period;`
  line
  line `(iii) the total number of each category of security actually delivered at each clearing;`
  line
  line `(d) the publication by the clearing house of all or any of the particulars submitted to the`
  line `^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India] under clause (c) subject to the directions, if any, issued by`
  line `the ^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India] in this behalf;`
  line
  line `(e) the regulation or prohibition of blank transfers;`
  line
  line `(f) the number and classes of contracts in respect of which settlements shall be made or`
  line `differences paid through the clearing house;`
  line
  line `(g) the regulation, or prohibition of budlas or carry-over facilities;`
  line
  line `(h) the fixing, altering or postponing of days for settlements;`
  line
  line `(i) the determination and declaration of market rates, including the opening, closing, highest and`
  line `lowest rates for securities;`
  line
  line `(j) the terms, conditions and incidents of contracts, including the prescription of margin`
  line `requirements, if any, and conditions relating thereto, and the forms of contracts in writing;`
  line
  line `(k) the regulation of the entering into, making, performance, rescission and termination, of`
  line `contracts, including contracts between members or between a member and his constituent or between`
  line `a member and a person who is not a member, and the consequences of default or insolvency on the`
  line `part of a seller or buyer or intermediary, the consequences of a breach or omission by a seller or`
  line `buyer, and the responsibility of members who are not parties to such contracts;`
  line
  line `(l) the regulation of taravani business including the placing of limitations thereon;`
  line
  line `(m) the listing of securities on the stock exchange, the inclusion of any security for the purpose of`
  line `dealings and the suspension or withdrawal of any such securities, and the suspension or prohibition of`
  line `trading in any specified securities;`
  line
  line `(n) the method and procedure for the settlement of claims or disputes, including settlement by`
  line arbitration;
  line
  line `(o) the levy and recovery of fees, fines and penalties;`
  line
  line `(p) the regulation of the course of business between parties to contracts in any capacity;`
  line
  line `(q) the fixing of a scale of brokerage and other charges;`
  line
  line `(r) the making, comparing, settling and closing of bargains;`
  line
  line `(s) the emergencies in trade which may arise, whether as a result of pool or syndicated operations`
  line `or cornering or otherwise, and the exercise of powers in such emergencies, including the power to fix`
  line `maximum and minimum prices for securities;`
  line
  line `(t) the regulation of dealings by members for their own account;`
  line
  line `(u) the separation of the functions of jobbers and brokers;`
  line
  line `(v) the limitations on the volume of trade done by any individual member in exceptional`
  line circumstances;
  line
  line `(w) the obligation of members to supply such information or explanation and to produce such`
  line `documents relating to the business as the governing body may require.`
  line
  line `(3) The bye-laws made under this section may--`
  line
  line `(a) specify the bye-laws the contravention of which shall make a contract entered into otherwise`
  line `than in accordance with the bye-laws void under sub-section (1) of section14;`
  line
  line `(b) provide that the contravention of any of the bye-laws shall render the member concerned`
  line `liable to one or more of the following punishments, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) fine;`
  line
  line `(ii) expulsion from membership;`
  line
  line `(iii) suspension from membership for a specified period;`
  line
  line `(iv) any other penalty of a like nature not involving the payment of money.`
  line
  line `(4) Any bye-laws made under this section shall be subject to such conditions in regard to previous`
  line `publication as may be prescribed, and, when approved by the ^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India],`
  line `shall be published in the Gazette of India and also in the Official Gazette of the State in which the`
  line `principal office of the recognised stock exchange is situate, and shall have effect as from the date of its`
  line `publication in the Gazette of India:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the ^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India] is satisfied in any case that in the`
  line `interest of the trade or in the public interest any bye-laws should be made immediately, it may, by order in`
  line `writing specifying the reasons therefor, dispense with the condition of previous publication.`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (14386)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of Securities and Exchange Board of India to make or amend bye-laws of recognised stock exchanges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14386&sectionno=10&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `10. Power of ^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India] to make or amend byelaws of`
  line `recognised stock exchanges.-- (1) The ^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India] may, either on a`
  line `request in writing received by it in this behalf from the governing body of a recognised stock exchange or`
  line `on its own motion, if it is satisfied after consultation with the governing body of the stock exchange that it`
  line `is necessary or expedient so to do and after recording its reasons for so doing, make bye-laws for all or`
  line `any of the matters specified in section 9 or amend any bye-laws made by such stock exchange under that`
  line section.
  line
  line `(2) Where in pursuance of this section any bye-laws have been made or amended, the due-laws so`
  line `made or amended shall be published in the Gazette of India and also in the Official Gazette of the State in`
  line `which the principal office of the recognised stock exchange is situate, and on the publication thereof in`
  line `the Gazette of India, the bye-laws so made or amended shall have effect as if they had been made or`
  line `amended by the recognised stock exchange concerned.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in this section, where the governing body of a recognised`
  line `stock exchange objects to any bye-laws made or amended under this section by the ^1[Securities and Exchange Board of India] on its own motion, it may, within ^2[two months] of the publication thereof in`
  line `the Gazette of India under sub-section (2) , apply to the ^3[Securities and Exchange Board of India] for`
  line `revision thereof, and the ^3[Securities and Exchange Board of India] may, after giving an opportunity to`
  line `the governing body of the stock exchange to be heard in the matter, revise the bye-laws so made or`
  line `amended, and where any bye-laws so made or amended are revised as a result of any action taken under`
  line `this sub-section, the bye-laws so revised shall be published and shall become effective as provided in`
  line `sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(4) The making or the amendment or revision of any bye-laws under this section shall in all cases be`
  line `subject to the condition of previous publication:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the ^3[Securities and Exchange Board of India] is satisfied in any case that in the`
  line `interest of the trade or in the public interest any bye-laws should be made, amended or revised`
  line `immediately, it may, by order in writing specifying the reasons therefor, dispense with the condition of`
  line `previous publication.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1992, s. 33 and the Schedule, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 30-1-1992).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 20, for "six months" (w,e,f, 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 15 of 1992, s. 33 and the Schedule, for "Central Government" (w.e.f. 30-1-1992).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (14387)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 16
  title `Power of Central Government to supersede governing body of a recognised stock exchange.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14387&sectionno=11&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to any other powers vested in the Central Government under this Act,`
  line `where the Central Government is of opinion that the governing body of any recognised stock exchange`
  line `should be superseded, then, notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, the Central Government may serve on the governing body a written notice that the Central`
  line `Government is considering the supersession of the governing body for the reasons specified in the notice`
  line `and after giving an opportunity to the governing body to be heard in the matter it may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, declare the governing body of such stock exchange to be superseded, and may`
  line `appoint any person or persons to exercise and perform all the powers and duties of the governing body,`
  line `and, where more persons than one are appointed, may appoint one of such persons to be the chairman and`
  line `another to be the vice-chairman thereof.`
  line
  line `(2) On the publication of a notification in the Official Gazette under sub-section (1), the following`
  line `consequences shall ensue, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the members of the governing body which has been superseded shall, as from the date of the`
  line `notification of supersession, cease to hold office as such members;`
  line
  line `(b) the person or persons appointed under sub-section (1) may exercise and perform all the`
  line `powers and duties of the governing body which has been superseded;`
  line
  line `(c) all such property of the recognised stock exchange as the person or persons appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1) may, by order in writing, specify in this behalf as being necessary for the purpose of`
  line `enabling him or them to carry on the business of the stock exchange, shall vest in such person or`
  line persons.
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any law or the rules or bye-laws of the`
  line `recognised stock exchange the governing body of which is superseded under sub-section (1), the person`
  line `or persons appointed under that sub-section shall hold office for such period as may be specified in the`
  line `notification published under that sub-section, and the Central Government may from time to time, by like`
  line `notification, vary such period.`
  line
  line `(4) The Central Government may at any time before the determination of the period of office of any`
  line `person or persons appointed under this section call upon the recognised stock exchange to re-constitute`
  line `the governing body in accordance with its rules and on such re-constitution all the property of the`
  line `recognised stock exchange which has vested in, or was in the possession of, the person or persons`
  line `appointed under sub-section (1) shall re-vest or vest, as the case may be, in the governing body so`
  line `re-constituted:`
  line
  line `Provided that until a governing body is so re-constituted, the person or persons appointed under`
  line `sub-section (1), shall continue to exercise and perform their powers and duties.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (14388)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to suspend business of recognised stock exchanges.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 56 of 1974, s. 2 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 20-12-1974)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14388&sectionno=12&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `If in the opinion of the Central`
  line `Government an emergency has risen and for the purpose of meeting the emergency the Central`
  line `Government considers it expedient so to do, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, for reasons to`
  line `be set out therein, direct a recognised stock exchange to suspend such of its business for such period not`
  line `exceeding seven days and subject to such conditions as may be specified in the notification, and, if, in the`
  line `opinion of the Central Government, the interest of the trade or the public interest requires that the period`
  line `should be extended, may, by like notification extend the said period from time to time:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the period of suspension is to be extended beyond the first period, no notification`
  line `extending the period of suspension shall be issued unless the governing body of the ^1[recognised`
  line `association stock exchange] has been given an opportunity of being heard in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (14389)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 18
  title `Power to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14389&sectionno=12A&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Power to issue directions.-- ^2[1] If, after making or causing to be made an inquiry, the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India is satisfied it is necessary--`
  line
  line `(a) in the interest of investors, or orderly development of securities market;`
  line
  line `(b) to prevent the affairs of any recognised stock exchange or clearing corporation, or such other`
  line `agency or person, providing trading or clearing or settlement facility in respect of securities, being`
  line `conducted in a manner detrimental to the interests of investors or securities market; or`
  line
  line `(c) to secure the proper management of any such stock exchange or clearing corporation or`
  line `agency or person, referred to in clause (b),`
  line `it may issue such directions, --`
  line
  line `(i) to any stock exchange or clearing corporation or agency or person referred to in clause (b)`
  line `or any person or class of persons associated with the securities market; or`
  line
  line `(ii) to any company whose securities are listed or proposed to be listed in a recognised stock`
  line exchange,
  line
  line `as may be appropriate in the interests of investors in securities and the securities market.]`
  line
  line `^3[iExplanation.--For the removal of doubts, it is hereby declared that power to issue directions under`
  line `this section shall include and always be deemed to have been included the power to direct any person,`
  line `who made profit or averted loss by indulging in any transaction or activity in contravention of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or regulations made thereunder, to disgorge an amount equivalent to the wrongful`
  line `gain made or loss averted by such contravention.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Without prejudice to the provisions of sub-section (1) and section 23-I, the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India may, by an order, for reasons to be recorded in writing, levy penalty under`
  line `section 23A, 23B, 23D, 23E, 23F, 23G, 23GA and 23H after holding an inquiry in the prescribed`
  line manner.]
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 6 (w.e.f 12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Section 12A numbered as thereof by sub-section (1) by Act 13 of 2018, s. 147 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 24 (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 147 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (14390)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 19
  title `Contracts in notified areas illegal in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14390&sectionno=13&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `If the Central Government is`
  line `satisfied, having regard to the nature or the volume of transactions in securities in any ^2[State or States or`
  line `area], that is necessary so to do, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare this section to`
  line `apply to such ^1[State or States or area], and thereupon every contract in such ^1[State or States or area] which is entered into after the date of the notification otherwise than ^3[between members of a recognised`
  line `stock exchange or recognised stock exchanges] in such ^1[State or States or area] or through or with such`
  line `member shall be illegal.`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that any contract entered into between members of two or more recognised stock`
  line `exchanges in such State or States or area, shall--`
  line
  line `(i) be subject to such terms and conditions as may be stipulated by the respective stock exchanges`
  line `with prior approval of Securities and Exchange Board of India;`
  line
  line `(ii) require prior permission from the respective stock exchanges if so stipulated by the stock`
  line `exchanges with prior approval of the Securities and Exchange Board of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 24 (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 7, for State or area (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for between members of a recognised stock exchange (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `4. The proviso ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (14391)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 20
  title `Additional trading floor.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 21 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14391&sectionno=13A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[13A. Additional trading floor.--A stock exchange may establish additional trading floor with the`
  line `prior approval of the Securities and Exchange Board of India in accordance with the terms and conditions`
  line `stipulated by the said Board.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section, "additional trading floor" means a trading ring or`
  line `trading facility offered by a recognised stock exchange outside its area of operation to enable the investors`
  line `to buy and sell securities through such trading floor under the regulatory framework of that stock`
  line exchange.]
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (14392)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 21
  title `Contracts in notified areas to be void in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14392&sectionno=14&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any contract entered`
  line `into in any State or area specified in the notification under section 13 which is in contravention of any of`
  line `the bye-laws specified in that behalf under clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 9 shall be void--`
  line
  line `(i) as respects the rights of any member of the recognised stock exchange who has entered into`
  line `such contract in contravention of any such bye-law, and also`
  line
  line `(ii) as respects the rights of any other person who has knowingly participated in the transaction`
  line `entailing such contravention.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be construed to affect the right of any person other than a member`
  line `of the recognised stock exchange to enforce any such contract or to recover any sum under or in respect`
  line `of such contract if such person had no knowledge that the transaction was in contravention of any of the`
  line `bye-laws specified in clause (a) of sub-section (3) of section 9.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (14393)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 22
  title `Members may not act as principals in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14393&sectionno=15&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No member of a recognised`
  line `stock exchange shall in respect of any securities enter into any contract as a principal with any person`
  line `other than a member of a recognised stock exchange, unless he has secured the consent or authority of`
  line `such person and discloses in the note, memorandum or agreement of sale or purchase that he is acting as a`
  line `principal:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the member has secured the consent or authority of such person otherwise than in`
  line `writing he shall secure written confirmation by such persons of such consent or authority within three`
  line `days from the date of the contract:`
  line
  line `Provided further that no such written consent or authority of such person shall be necessary for`
  line `closing out any outstanding contract entered into by such person in accordance with the bye-laws, if the`
  line `member discloses in the note, memorandum or agreement of sale or purchase in respect of such closing`
  line `out that he is acting as a principal.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (14394)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to prohibit contracts in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14394&sectionno=16&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is of opinion that`
  line `it is necessary to prevent undesirable speculations in specified securities in any State or area, it may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, declare that no person in the State or area specified in the notification`
  line `shall, save with the permission of the Central Government, enter into any contract for the sale or purchase`
  line `of any security specified in the notification except to the extent and in the manner, if any, specified`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(2) All contracts in contravention of the provisions of sub-section (1) entered into after the date of the`
  line `notification issued thereunder shall be illegal.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (14395)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 24
  title `Licensing of dealers in securities in certain areas.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1992, s. 33 and the Schedule, for "licence granted by the Central Government" (w.e.f 30-1-1992)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14395&sectionno=17&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of`
  line `sub-section (3) and to the other provisions contained in this Act, no person shall carry on or purport to`
  line `carry on, whether on his own behalf or on behalf of any other person, the business of dealing in securities`
  line `in any State or area to which section 13 has not been declared to apply and to which the Central`
  line `Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare this section to apply, except under the`
  line `authority of a ^1[licence granted by the Securities and Exchange Board of India] in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) No notification under sub-section (1) shall be issued with respect to any State or area unless the`
  line `Central Government is satisfied, having regard to the manner in which securities are being dealt with in`
  line `such State or area, that it is desirable or expedient in the interest of the trade or in the public interest that`
  line `such dealings should be regulated by a system of licensing.`
  line
  line `(3) The restrictions imposed by sub-section (1) in relation to dealings in securities shall not apply to`
  line `the doing of anything by or on behalf of a member of any recognised stock exchange.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (14396)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 25
  title `Public issue and listing of securities referred to in sub-clause (ie) of clause (h) of section 2.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2007, s. 3 (w.e.f. 28-5-2007).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14396&sectionno=17A&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[17A. Public issue and listing of securities referred to in sub-clause (ie) of clause (h) of`
  line `section 2.--(1) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in this Act or any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, no securities of the nature referred to in sub-clause (ie) of clause (h) of section 2 shall be`
  line `offered to the public or listed on any recognised stock exchange unless the issuer fulfils such eligibility`
  line `criteria and complies with such other requirements as may be specified by regulations made by the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India.`
  line
  line `(2) Every issuer referred to in sub-clause (ie) of clause (h) of section 2 intending to offer the`
  line `certificates or instruments referred therein to the public shall make an application, before issuing the offer`
  line `document to the public, to one or more recognised stock exchanges for permission for such certificates or`
  line `instruments to be listed on the stock exchange or each such stock exchange.`
  line
  line `(3) Where the permission applied for under sub-section (2) for listing has not been granted or refused`
  line `by the recognised stock exchanges or any of them, the issuer shall forthwith repay all moneys, if any,`
  line `received from applicants in pursuance of the offer document, and if any such money is not repaid within`
  line `eight days after the issuer becomes liable to repay it, the issuer and every director or trustee thereof, as the`
  line `case may be, who is in default shall, on and from the expiry of the eighth day, be jointly and severally`
  line `liable to repay that money with interest at the rate of fifteen per cent. per annum.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In reckoning the eighth day after another day, any intervening day which is a public`
  line `holiday under the Negotiable Instruments Act, 1881(26 of 1881), shall be disregarded, and if the eighth`
  line `day (as so reckoned) is itself such a public holiday, there shall for the said purposes be substituted the first`
  line `day thereafter which is not a holiday.`
  line
  line `(4) All the provisions of this Act relating to listing of securities of a public company on a recognised`
  line `stock exchange shall, mutatis mutandis, apply to the listing of the securities of the nature referred to in`
  line `sub-clause (ie) of clause (h) of section 2 by the issuer, being a special purpose distinct entity.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (14397)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 26
  title `Exclusion of spot delivery contracts from sections 13, 14, 15 and 17.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14397&sectionno=18&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) Nothing contained`
  line `in sections 13, 14, 15 and 17 shall apply to spot delivery contracts.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if the Central Government is of opinion`
  line `that in the interest of the trade or in the public interest it is expedient to regulate and control the business`
  line `of delaying in spot delivery contracts also in any State or area (whether section 13 has been declared to`
  line `apply to that State or area or not), it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare that the`
  line `provisions of section 17 shall also apply to such State or area in respect of spot delivery contracts`
  line `generally or in respect of spot delivery contracts for the sale or purchase of such securities as may be`
  line `specified in the notification, and may also specify the manner in which, and the extent to which, the`
  line `provisions of that section shall so apply.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (14398)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 27
  title `Contracts in derivatives.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14398&sectionno=18A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. Contracts in derivatives.--Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the lime`
  line `being in force, contracts in derivative shall be legal and valid if such contracts are--`
  line
  line `(a) traded on a recognised stock exchange;`
  line
  line `(b) settled on the clearing house of the recognised ^2[stock exchange; or] in accordance with the`
  line `rules and bye-laws of such stock exchange.]`
  line
  line `^3[(c) between such parties and on such terms as the Central Government may, by notification in`
  line `the Official Gazette, specify.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 3 (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 134, for "stock exchange ," (w.e.f. 14-5-2015)`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 134 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015)`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (14399)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 28
  title `Stock exchanges other than recognised stock exchanges prohibited.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14399&sectionno=19&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) No person shall,`
  line `except with the permission of the Central Government, organise or assist in organising or be a member of`
  line `any stock exchange (other than a recognised stock exchange) for the purpose of assisting in, entering into`
  line `or performing any contracts in securities.`
  line
  line `(2) This section shall come into force in any State or area on such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (14400)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 29
  title [Omitted.].
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14400&sectionno=20&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `[Prohibition of options in securities.] Omitted by the Securities Laws (Amendment) Act, 1995`
  line `(9 of 1995), s. 22 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (14401)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 30
  title `Conditions for listing.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 23, for section 21 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14401&sectionno=21&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Conditions for listing.--Where securities are listed on the application of any person if any`
  line `recognised stock exchange, such person shall comply with the conditions of the listing agreement with`
  line `that stock exchange.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (14402)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 31
  title `Delisting of securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 8 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14402&sectionno=21A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[21A. Delisting of securities.--(1) A recognised stock exchange may delist the securities, after`
  line `recording the reasons therefor, from any recognised stock exchange on any of the ground or grounds as`
  line `may be prescribed under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that the securities of a company shall not be delisted unless the company concerned has`
  line `been given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.`
  line
  line `(2) A listed company or an aggrieved investor may file an appeal before the Securities Appellate`
  line `Tribunal against the decision of the recognised stock exchange delisting the securities within fifteen days`
  line `from the date of the decision of the recognised stock exchange delisting the securities and the provisions`
  line `of sections 22B to 22E of this Act, shall apply, as far as may be, to such appeals:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Securities Appellate Tribunal may, if it is satisfied that the company was prevented`
  line `by sufficient cause from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period`
  line `not exceeding one month.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (14403)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 32
  title `Right of appeal against refusal by stock exchanges to list securities of public companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14403&sectionno=22&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^2[22. Right of appeal against refusal by stock exchanges to list securities of public`
  line `companies.--Where a recognised stock exchange acting in pursuance of any power given to it by its`
  line `bye-laws, refuses to list the securities of any public company ^3[or collective investment scheme], the`
  line `company ^1[or scheme] shall be entitled to be furnished with the reasons for such refusal, and may,--`
  line
  line `(a) within fifteen days from the date on which the reasons for such refusal are furnished to it, or`
  line
  line `(b) where the stock exchange has omitted or failed to dispose of, within the time specified in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 73 of the Companies Act,1956 (1 of 1956) (hereafter in this section referred`
  line `to as the "specified time"), the application for permission for the shares or debentures to be dealt with`
  line `on the stock exchange, within fifteen days from the date of expiry of specified time or within such`
  line `further period, not exceeding one month, as the Central Government may, on sufficient cause being`
  line `shown, allow,`
  line
  line `appeal to the Central Government against such refusal, omission of failure, as the case may be, and`
  line `thereupon the Central Government may, after giving the stock exchange an opportunity of being heard,--`
  line
  line `(i) vary or set aside the decision of the stock exchange, or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the stock exchange has omitted or failed to dispose of the application within the`
  line `specified time, grant or refuse the permission,`
  line
  line `and where the Central Government sets aside the decision of the recognised stock exchange or grants the`
  line `permission, the stock exchange shall act in conformity with the orders of the Central Government:]`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[Provided that no appeal shall be preferred against refusal, omission or failure, as the case may be,`
  line `under this section on and after the commencement of the Securities Laws (Second Amendment) Act, 1999`
  line `(32 of 1999).]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 23, for section 21 (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 1974, s. 42, for section 22 (w.e.f. 1-2-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 5 (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
  line
  line `4. The proviso ins. by Act 32 of 1999, s. 4 (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_22_a:
  sectionId (14404)
  sectionNo 22A
  orderNo 33
  title `Right of appeal to Securities Appellate Tribunal against refusal of stock exchange to list securities of public companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14404&sectionno=22A&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_22_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[22A. Right of appeal to Securities Appellate Tribunal against refusal of stock exchange to list`
  line `securities of public companies.--(1) Where a recognised stock exchange, acting in pursuance of any`
  line `power given to it by its bye-laws, refuses to list the securities of any company, the company shall be`
  line `entitled to be furnished with reasons for such refusal, and may,--`
  line
  line `(a) within fifteen days from the date on which the reasons for such refusal are furnished to it, or`
  line
  line `(b) where the stock exchange has omitted or failed to dispose of, within the time specified in`
  line `sub-section (1A) of section 73 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956) (hereafter in this section`
  line `referred to as the "specified time"), the application for permission for the shares or debentures to be`
  line `dealt with on the stock exchange, within fifteen days from the date of expiry of the specified time or`
  line `within such further period, not exceeding one month, as the Securities Appellate Tribunal may, on`
  line `sufficient cause being shown, allow,`
  line
  line `appeal to the Securities Appellate Tribunal having jurisdiction in the matter against such refusal, omission`
  line `or failure, as the case may be, and thereupon the Securities Appellate Tribunal may, after giving the stock`
  line `exchange, an opportunity of being heard,--`
  line
  line `(i) vary or set aside the decision of the stock exchange; or`
  line
  line `(ii) where the stock exchange has omitted or failed to dispose of the application within the`
  line `specified time, grant or refuse the permission,`
  line
  line `and where the Securities Appellate Tribunal sets aside the decision of the recognised stock exchange or`
  line `grants the permission, the stock exchange shall act in conformity with the orders of the Securities`
  line `Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be in such form and be accompanied by such fee as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Securities Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the Board and`
  line `parties to the appeal.`
  line
  line `(4) The appeal filed before the Securities Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with`
  line `by it as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal finally within`
  line `six months from the date of receipt of the appeal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_b:
  sectionId (14405)
  sectionNo 22B
  orderNo 34
  title `Procedure and powers of Securities Appellate tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14405&sectionno=22B&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_22_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[22B. Procedure and powers of Securities Appellate tribunal--(1) The Securities Appellate`
  line `Tribunal shall not be bound by the procedure laid down by the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908),`
  line `but shall be guided by the principles of natural justice and, subject to the other provisions of this Act and`
  line `of any rules, the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall have powers to regulate their own procedure`
  line `including the places at which they shall have their sittings.`
  line
  line `(2) The Securities Appellate Tribunal shall have, for the purpose of discharging their functions under`
  line `this Act, the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents;`
  line
  line `(e) reviewing its decisions;`
  line
  line `(f) dismissing an application for default or deciding it ex parte;`
  line
  line `(g) setting aside any order of dismissal of any application for default or any order passed by it`
  line `ex parte; and`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every proceeding before the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a judicial`
  line `proceeding within the meaning of sections 193 and 228, and for the purposes of section 196 of the Indian`
  line `Penal Code (45 of 1860) and the Securities Appellate Tribunal shall be deemed to be a civil court for all`
  line `the purposes of section 195 and Chapter XXVI of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_c:
  sectionId (14406)
  sectionNo 22C
  orderNo 35
  title `Right to legal representation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14406&sectionno=22C&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_22_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[22C. Right to legal representation.--The appellant may either appear in person or authorise one or`
  line `more chartered accountants or company secretaries or cost accountants or legal practitioners or any of its`
  line `officers to present his or its case before the Securities Appellate Tribunal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "chartered accountant" means a chartered accountant as defined in clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Chartered Accountants Act, 1949 (38 of 1949) and who has`
  line `obtained a certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(b) "company secretary" means a company secretary as defined in clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 2 of the Company Secretaries Act, 1980 (56 of 1980) and who has obtained`
  line `a certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "cost accountant" means a cost accountant as defined in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 2 of the Cost and Works Accountants Act, 1959 (23 of 1959) and who has obtained a`
  line `certificate of practice under sub-section (1) of section 6 of that Act;`
  line
  line `(d) "legal practitioner" means an advocate, vakil or an attorney of any High Court, and includes a`
  line `pleader in practice.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_d:
  sectionId (14407)
  sectionNo 22D
  orderNo 36
  title Limitation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14407&sectionno=22D&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_22_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[22D. Limitation.--The provisions of the Limitation Act, 1963 (36 of 1963) shall, as far as may be,`
  line `apply to an appeal made to a Securities Appellate Tribunal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_e:
  sectionId (14408)
  sectionNo 22E
  orderNo 37
  title `Civil Court not to have jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14408&sectionno=22E&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_22_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[22E. Civil Court not to have jurisdiction.--No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any`
  line `suit or proceeding in respect of any matter which a Securities Appellate Tribunal is empowered by or`
  line `under this Act to determine and no injunction shall be granted by any court or other authority in respect of`
  line `any action taken or to be taken in pursuance of any power conferred by or under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22_f:
  sectionId (14409)
  sectionNo 22F
  orderNo 38
  title `Appeal to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-12-1999).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14409&sectionno=22F&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_22_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[22F. Appeal to High Court.--Any person aggrieved by any decision or order of the Securities`
  line `Appellate Tribunal may file an appeal to the High Court within sixty days from the date of`
  line `communication of the decision or order of the Securities Appellate Tribunal to him on any question of`
  line `fact or law arising out of such order:`
  line
  line `Provided that the High Court may, if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause`
  line `from filing the appeal within the said period, allow it to be filed within a further period not exceeding`
  line `sixty days.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (14410)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 39
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14410&sectionno=23&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person who--`
  line
  line `(a) without reasonable excuse (the burden of proving which shall be on him) fails to comply with`
  line `any requisition made under sub-section (4) of section 6; or`
  line
  line `(b) enters into any contract in contravention of any of the provisions contained in section 13 or`
  line `section 16; or`
  line
  line `(c) contravenes the provisions contained in ^1[section 17 or section 17A], or section 19; or`
  line
  line `^2[(d) enters into any contract in derivative in contravention of section 18A or the rules made`
  line `under section 30.]`
  line
  line `(e) owns or keeps a place other than that of a recognised stock exchange which is used for the`
  line `purpose of entering into or performing any contracts in contravention of any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act and knowingly permits such place to be used for such purposes; or`
  line
  line `(f) manages, controls, or assists in keeping any place other than that of a recognised stock`
  line `exchange which is used for the purpose of entering into or performing any contracts in contravention`
  line `of any of the provisions of this Act or at which contracts are recorded or adjusted or rights or`
  line `liabilities arising out of contracts are adjusted, regulated or enforced in any manner whatsoever; or`
  line
  line `(g) not being a member of a recognised stock exchange or his agent authorised as such under the`
  line `rules or bye-laws of such stock exchange or not being a dealer in securities licensed under section 17`
  line `wilfully represents to or induces any person to believe that contracts can be entered into or performed`
  line `under this Act through him; or`
  line
  line `(h) not being a member of a recognised stock exchange or his agent authorised as such under the`
  line `rules or bye-laws of such stock exchange or not being a dealer in securities licensed under section 17,`
  line `canvasses, advertises or touts in any manner either for himself or on behalf of any other persons for`
  line `any business connected with contracts in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act; or`
  line
  line `(i) joins, gathers or assists in gathering at any place other than the place of business specified in`
  line `the bye-laws of a recognised stock exchange any person or persons for making bids or offers or for`
  line `entering into or performing any contracts in contravention of any of the provisions of this Act;`
  line
  line `^3[shall, without prejudice to any award of penalty by the Adjudicating Officer ^4[or the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India] under this Act, on conviction, be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to ten years or with fine, which may extend to twenty-five crore rupees or with both]`
  line
  line `(2) Any person who enters into any contract in contravention of the provisions contained in section 15`
  line `^5[or who fails to comply with the provisions of ^6[section 21 or section 21A] or with the orders of] or who`
  line `or section 22 ^7[or with the orders of the Securities Appellate Tribunal] shall, on conviction, be punishable`
  line `with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2007, s. 4, for "section 17" (w.e.f. 28-5-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 6 (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 21, for certain words (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 148 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 9 of 1995, s. 24, for "or who fails to comply with the orders of the Securities and Exchange Board of India under`
  line `section 21" (w.e.f. 25-1-1995).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 10, for "section 21" (w.e.f. 12-10-2004)`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 32 of 1999, s. 6 (w.e.f. 16-10-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a:
  sectionId (14411)
  sectionNo 23A
  orderNo 40
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish information, return, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14411&sectionno=23A&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[23A. Penalty for failure to furnish information, return, etc.--Any person, who is required under`
  line `this Act or any rules made thereunder,--`
  line
  line `(a) to furnish any information, document, books, returns or ^2[report to a recognised stock`
  line `exchange or to the Board, fails to furnish the same within the time specified therefor in the listing`
  line `agreement or conditions or bye-laws of the recognised stock exchange or the Act or rules made`
  line `thereunder, or who furnishes] ^3[false, incorrect or incomplete information, document, books, return or`
  line `report], shall be liable to a penalty ^4[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may`
  line `extend to one lakh rupees for each during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one`
  line `crore rupees], whichever is less for each such failure;`
  line
  line `(b) to maintain books of account or records, as per the listing agreement or conditions, or`
  line `bye-laws of a recognised stock exchange, fails to maintain the same, shall be liable to a`
  line `penalty ^1[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for`
  line `each day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore rupees].]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 11 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 2019, s. 146, for certain words (w.e.f. 20-1-2020).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 149 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 25, for "of one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues or one crore rupees,`
  line `whichever is less" (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_b:
  sectionId (14412)
  sectionNo 23B
  orderNo 41
  title `Penalty for failure by any person to enter into an agreement with clients.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14412&sectionno=23B&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_b_content:
  string
  line `If any person,`
  line `who is required under this Act or any bye-laws of a recognised stock exchange made thereunder, to enter`
  line `into an agreement with his client, fails to enter into such an agreement, he shall be liable to a penalty ^1[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees for each`
  line `day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore rupees] for every such failure.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 26, for "of one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues or one crore rupees,`
  line `whichever is less" (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_c:
  sectionId (14413)
  sectionNo 23C
  orderNo 42
  title `Penalty for failure to redress Investors grievances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14413&sectionno=23C&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_c_content:
  string
  line `If any stock broker or sub-broker or a`
  line `company whose securities are listed or proposed to be listed in a recognised stock exchange, after having`
  line `been called upon by the Securities and Exchange Board of India or a recognised stock exchange in`
  line `writing, to redress the grievances of the investors, fails to redress such grievances within the time`
  line `stipulated by the Securities and Exchange Board of India or a recognised stock exchange, he or it shall be`
  line `liable to a penalty ^1[which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one lakh rupees`
  line `for each day during which such failure continues subject to a maximum of one crore rupees].]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_c_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 27, ibid., for "of one lakh rupees for each day during which such failure continues or one crore rupees, whichever is`
  line `less" (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_d:
  sectionId (14414)
  sectionNo 23D
  orderNo 43
  title `Penalty for failure to segregate securities or moneys of client or clients.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 28, ibid., for "liable to a penalty not exceeding one crore rupees" (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14414&sectionno=23D&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_d_content:
  string
  line `If any person, who`
  line `is registered under section 12 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) as a`
  line `stock broker or sub-broker, fails to segregate securities or moneys of the client or clients or uses the`
  line `securities or moneys of a client or clients for self or for any other client, he shall be ^1[liable to a penalty`
  line `which shall not be less than one lakh rupees but which may extend to one crore rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_23_e:
  sectionId (14415)
  sectionNo 23E
  orderNo 44
  title `Penalty for failure to comply with provision of listing conditions or delisting conditions or grounds.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_e_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_e_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14415&sectionno=23E&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_e_content:
  string
  line `If a company or any person managing collective investment scheme or mutual fund ^1[or real`
  line `estate investment trust or infrastructure investment trust or alternative investment fund], fails to comply`
  line `with the listing conditions or delisting conditions or grounds or commits a breach thereof, it or he shall`
  line `be ^2[liable to a penalty which shall not be less than five lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty-five`
  line `crore rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_23_e_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 150 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 29, for "liable to a penalty not exceeding twenty-five crore rupees" (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_f:
  sectionId (14416)
  sectionNo 23F
  orderNo 45
  title `Penalty for excess dematerialisation or delivery of unlisted securities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_f_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 30, ibid., for "liable to a penalty not exceeding twenty-five crore rupees" (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14416&sectionno=23F&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_f_content:
  string
  line `If any issuer`
  line `dematerialises securities more than the issued securities of a company or delivers in the stock exchanges`
  line `the securities which are not listed in the recognised stock exchange or delivers securities where no trading`
  line `permission has been given by the recognised stock exchange, he shall be ^1[liable to a penalty which shall`
  line `not be less than five lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty-five crore rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_23_g:
  sectionId (14417)
  sectionNo 23G
  orderNo 46
  title `Penalty for failure to furnish periodical returns, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_g_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_g_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14417&sectionno=23G&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_g_content:
  string
  line `If a recognised stock exchange fails or`
  line `neglects to furnish periodical returns ^1[or furnishes false, incorrect or incomplete periodical returns] to the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India or fails or neglects to make or amend its rules or bye-laws as`
  line `directed by the Securities and Exchange Board of India or fails to comply with directions issued by the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India, such recognised stock exchange shall be ^2[liable to a penalty`
  line `which shall not be less than five lakh rupees but which may extend to twenty-five crore rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_23_g_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2019, s. 151 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 31, for "liable to a penalty not exceeding twenty-five crore rupees" (w.ef. 8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_ga:
  sectionId (48891)
  sectionNo 23GA
  orderNo 47
  title `Penalty for failure to conduct business in accordance with rules, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_ga_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 152 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=48891&sectionno=23GA&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_ga_content:
  string
  line `^1[23GA. Penalty for failure to conduct business in accordance with rules, etc.--Where a stock`
  line `exchange or a clearing corporation fails to conduct its business with its members or any issuer or its agent`
  line `or any person associated with the securities markets in accordance with the rules or regulations mad by`
  line `the Securities and Exchange Board of India and the directions issued by it under this Act, the stock`
  line `exchange or the clearing corporations, as the case may be, shall be liable to penalty which shall not be`
  line `less than five crore rupees but which may extend to twenty-five crore rupees or three times the amount of`
  line `gains made out of such failure, whichever is higher.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_h:
  sectionId (14418)
  sectionNo 23H
  orderNo 48
  title `Penalty for contravention where no separate penalty has been provided.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_h_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_h_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14418&sectionno=23H&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[23H. Penalty for contravention where no separate penalty has been provided.--Whoever fails to`
  line `comply with any provision of this Act, the rules or articles or bye-laws or the regulations of the`
  line `recognised stock exchange or directions issued by the Securities and Exchange Board of India for which`
  line `no separate penalty has been provided, shall be ^2[liable to a penalty which shall not be less than one lakh`
  line `rupees but which may extend to one crore rupees].`
obj_root_law_sections_23_h_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 11 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 32, for “liable to a penalty not exceeding twenty-five crore rupess” (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_i:
  sectionId (14444)
  sectionNo 23-I
  orderNo 49
  title `Power to adjudicate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_i_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_i_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14444&sectionno=23-I&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_i_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of adjudging under sections 23A, 23B, 23C, 23D,`
  line `23E, 23F, 23G and 23H, the Securities and Exchange Board of India ^1[may] appoint any officer not below`
  line `the rank of a Division Chief of the Securities and Exchange Board of India to be an adjudicating officer`
  line `for holding an inquiry in the prescribed manner after giving any person concerned a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard for the purpose of imposing any penalty.`
  line
  line `(2) While holding an inquiry, the adjudicating officer shall have power to summon and enforce the`
  line `attendance of any person acquainted with the facts and circumstances of the case to give evidence or to`
  line `produce any document, which in the opinion of the adjudicating officer, may be useful for or relevant to the subject-matter of the inquiry and if, on such inquiry, he is satisfied that the person has failed to`
  line `comply with the provisions of any of the sections specified in sub-section (1), he may impose such`
  line `penalty as he thinks fit in accordance with the provisions of any of those sections.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(3) The Board may call for and examine the record of any proceedings under this section and if it`
  line `considers that the order passed by the adjudicating officer is erroneous to the extent it is not in the`
  line `interests of the securities market, it may, after making or causing to be made such inquiry as it deems`
  line `necessary, pass an order enhancing the quantum of penalty, if the circumstances of the case so justify:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be passed unless the person concerned has been given an`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter:`
  line
  line `Provided further that nothing contained in this sub-section shall be applicable after an expiry of a`
  line `period of three months from the date of the order passed by the adjudicating officer or disposal of the`
  line `appeal under section 23L, whichever is earlier.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_i_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2019, s. 153, for "shall" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 33 (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_j:
  sectionId (14445)
  sectionNo 23J
  orderNo 50
  title `Factors to be taken into account by the adjudicating officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_j_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_j_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14445&sectionno=23J&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_j_content:
  string
  line `23J. ^1[Factors to be taken into account while adjudging quantum of penalty.]--While adjudging`
  line `the quantum of penalty under ^2[section 12A or section 23-I],`
  line `^3[the Securities and Exchange Board of India`
  line `or the adjudicating officer] shall have due regard to the following factors, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the amount of disproportionate gain or unfair advantage, wherever quantifiable, made as a`
  line `result of the default;`
  line
  line `(b) the amount of loss caused to an investor or group of investors as a result of the default;`
  line
  line `(c) the repetitive nature of the default.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_j_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 13 of 2019, s. 154, for "Factors to be taken into account by adjudicating officer" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for "section 23-I" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 154, ibid., for "the adjudicating officer" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_ja:
  sectionId (14446)
  sectionNo 23JA
  orderNo 51
  title `Settlement of administrative and civil proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_ja_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_ja_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14446&sectionno=23JA&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_ja_content:
  string
  line `^1[23JA. Settlement of administrative and civil proceedings.--(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in any other law for the time being in force, any person, against whom any proceedings have`
  line `been initiated or may be initiated under section 12A or section 23-1, may file an application in writing to`
  line `the Board proposing for settlement of the proceedings initiated or to be initiated for the alleged defaults.`
  line
  line `(2) The Board may, after taking into consideration the nature, gravity and impact of defaults, agree to`
  line `the proposal for settlement, on payment of such sum by the defaulter or on such other terms as may be`
  line `determined by the Board in accordance with the regulations made under the Securities and Exchange`
  line `Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992).`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of settlement under this section, the procedure as specified by the Board under`
  line `the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act, 1992 (15 of 1992) shall apply.`
  line
  line `(4) No appeal shall lie under section 23L against any order passed by the Board or the adjudicating`
  line `officer, as the case may be, under this section.]`
  line
  line `^2[(5) All settlement amounts, excluding the disgorgement amount and legal costs, realised under this`
  line `Act shall be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_ja_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 34, ibid. (w.e.f. 20-4-2007).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 13 of 2019, s. 155 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_jb:
  sectionId (14447)
  sectionNo 23JB
  orderNo 52
  title `Recovery of amounts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_jb_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_jb_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14447&sectionno=23JB&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_jb_content:
  string
  line `^1[23JB. Recovery of amounts.--(1) If a person fails to pay the penalty imposed ^2[under this Act] or`
  line `fails to comply with a direction of disgorgement order issued under section 12A or fails to pay any fees`
  line `due to the Board, the Recovery Officer may draw up under his signature a statement in the specified form`
  line `specifying the amount due from the person (such statement being hereafter in this Chapter referred to as`
  line `certificate) and shall proceed to recover from such person the amount specified in the certificate by one or`
  line `more of the following modes, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) attachment and sale of the person's movable property;`
  line
  line `(b) attachment of the person's bank accounts;`
  line
  line `(c) attachment and sale of the person's immovable property;`
  line
  line `(d) arrest of the person and his detention in prison;`
  line
  line `(e) appointing a receiver for the management of the person's movable and immovable properties,`
  line `and for this purpose, the provisions of sections 220 to 227, 228A, 229, 232, the Second and Third`
  line `Schedules to the Income-tax Act, 1961(43 of 1961) and the Income-tax (Certificate Proceedings)`
  line `Rules, 1962, as in force from time to time, in so far as may be, apply with necessary modifications as`
  line `if the said provisions and the rules thereunder were the provisions of this Act and referred to the`
  line `amount due under this Act instead of to income-tax under the Income-tax Act, 1961.`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--For the purposes of this sub-section, the person's movable or immovable property or`
  line `monies held in bank accounts shall include any property or monies held in bank accounts which has been`
  line `transferred, directly or indirectly on or after the date when the amount specified in certificate had become`
  line `due, by the person to his spouse or minor child or son's wife or son's minor child, otherwise than for`
  line `adequate consideration, and which is held by, or stands in the name of, any of the persons aforesaid; and`
  line `so far as the movable or immovable property or monies held in bank accounts so transferred to his minor`
  line `child or his son's minor child is concerned, it shall, even after the date of attainment of majority by such`
  line `minor child or son's minor child, as the case may be, continue to be included in the person's movable or`
  line `immovable property or monies held in bank accounts for recovering any amount due from the person`
  line `under this Act.`
  line
  line `Explanation 2.--Any reference under the provisions of the Second and Third Schedules to the`
  line `Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961) and the Income-tax (Certificate Proceedings) Rules, 1962 to the`
  line `assessee shall be construed as a reference to the person specified in the certificate.`
  line
  line `Explanation 3.--Any reference to appeal in Chapter XVIID and the Second Schedule to the Incometax`
  line `Act, 1961(43 of 1961), shall be construed as a reference to appeal before the Securities Appellate`
  line `Tribunal under section 23L of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Recovery Officer shall be empowered to seek the assistance of the local district`
  line `administration while exercising the powers under sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, the recovery of`
  line `amounts by a Recovery Officer under sub-section (7), pursuant to non-compliance with any direction`
  line `issued by the Board under section 12A, shall have precedence over any other claim against such person.`
  line
  line `(4) For the purposes of sub-sections (1), (2) and (3), the expression Recovery Officer means any`
  line `officer of the Board who may be authorised, by general or special order in writing to exercise the powers`
  line `of a Recovery Officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_jb_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 35. (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 156, for "by the adjudicating officer" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_jc:
  sectionId (48892)
  sectionNo 23JC
  orderNo 53
  title `Continuance of proceedings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_jc_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 157 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=48892&sectionno=23JC&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_jc_content:
  string
  line `^1[23JC. Continuance of proceedings.--Where a person dies, his legal representative shall be liable`
  line `to pay any sum which the deceased would have been liable to pay, if he had not died, in the like manner`
  line `and to the same extent as the deceased:`
  line
  line `Provided that, in case of any penalty payable under this Act, a legal representative shall be liable only`
  line `in case the penalty has been imposed before the death of the deceased person.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purposes of sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(a) any proceeding for disgorgement, refund or an action for recovery before the Recovery`
  line `Officer under this Act, except a proceeding for levy of penalty, initiated against the deceased before`
  line `his death shall be deemed to have been initiated against the legal representative, and may be`
  line `continued against the legal representative from the stage at which it stood on the date of the death of`
  line `the deceased and all the provisions of this act shall apply accordingly;`
  line
  line `(b) any proceeding for disgorgement, refund or an action for recovery before the Recovery`
  line `Officer under this Act, except a proceeding for levy of penalty, which could have been initiated`
  line `against the deceased if he had survived, may be initiated against the legal representative and all the`
  line `provisions of this Act shall apply accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) Every legal representative shall be personally liable for any sum payable by him in his capacity as`
  line `legal representative if, while his liability for such sum remains undercharged, he creates a charge on or`
  line `disposes of or pasts with any assets of the estate of the deceased, which are in, or may come into, his`
  line `possession, but such liability shall be limited to the value of the asset so charged, disposed of or parted`
  line with.
  line
  line `(4) The liability of a legal representative under this section shall, be limited to the extent to which the`
  line `estate of the decreased is capable of meeting the liability.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this section "Legal representative" means a person who in law`
  line `represents the estate of a deceased person, and includes any person who intermeddles with the estate of`
  line `the deceased and where a party sued or is sued in a representative character, the person on whom the`
  line `estate devolves on the death of the party so suing or sued.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_k:
  sectionId (14448)
  sectionNo 23K
  orderNo 54
  title `Crediting sum realised by way of penalties to Consolidated Fund of India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_k_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_k_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14448&sectionno=23K&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_k_content:
  string
  line `All sums`
  line `realised by way of penalties under this Act shall be credited to the Consolidated Fund of India.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_k_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23_l:
  sectionId (14449)
  sectionNo 23L
  orderNo 55
  title `Appeal to Securities Appellate Tribunal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_l_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 36 (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14449&sectionno=23L&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_l_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved, by the order or decision`
  line `of the recognised stock exchange or the adjudicating officer or any order made by the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India under section 4B ^1[or sub-section (3) of section 23-I], may prefer an appeal`
  line `before the Securities Appellate Tribunal and the provisions of sections 22B, 22C, 22D and 22E of this`
  line `Act, shall apply, as far as may be, to such appeals.`
  line
  line `(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be filed within a period of forty-five days from the date`
  line `on which a copy of the order or decision is received by the appellant and it shall be in such form and be`
  line `accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Securities Appellate Tribunal may entertain an appeal after the expiry of the said`
  line `period of forty-five days if it is satisfied that there was sufficient cause for not filing it within that period.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (1), the Securities Appellate Tribunal may, after giving`
  line `the parties to the appeal, an opportunity of being heard, pass such orders thereon as it thinks fit,`
  line `confirming, modifying or setting aside the order appealed against.`
  line
  line `(4) The Securities Appellate Tribunal shall send a copy of every order made by it to the parties to the`
  line `appeal and to the concerned adjudicating officer.`
  line
  line `(5) The appeal filed before the Securities Appellate Tribunal under sub-section (1) shall be dealt with`
  line `by it as expeditiously as possible and endeavour shall be made by it to dispose of the appeal finally within`
  line `six months from the date of receipt of the appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_m:
  sectionId (14450)
  sectionNo 23M
  orderNo 56
  title Offences.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_m_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_m_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14450&sectionno=23M&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_m_content:
  string
  line `(1) Without prejudice to any award of penalty by the adjudicating officer ^1[or the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India] under this Act, if any person contravenes or attempts to`
  line `contravene or abets the contravention of the provisions of this Act or of any rules or regulations or byelaws`
  line `made thereunder, for which no punishment is provided elsewhere in this Act, he shall be punishable`
  line `with imprisonment for a term which may extend to ten years, or with fine, which may extend to twentyfive`
  line `crore rupees or with both.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person fails to pay the penalty imposed by the adjudicating officer ^1[or the Securities and`
  line `Exchange Board of India] or fails to comply with ^2[the direction or order], he shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than one month but which may extend to ten years, or`
  line `with fine, which may extend to twenty-five crore rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_m_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 158 (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 158, ibid., for "any of his directions or orders" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_23_n:
  sectionId (14451)
  sectionNo 23N
  orderNo 57
  title `Composition of certain offences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_n_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_n_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14451&sectionno=23N&orderno=57&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_n_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), any offence punishable under this Act, not being an offence`
  line `punishable with imprisonment only, or with imprisonment and also with fine, may either before or after`
  line `the institution of any proceeding, be compounded by a Securities Appellate Tribunal or a court before`
  line `which such proceedings are pending.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_n_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23_o:
  sectionId (14452)
  sectionNo 23-O
  orderNo 58
  title `Power to grant immunity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_o_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_o_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14452&sectionno=23-O&orderno=58&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_23_o_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, on recommendation by the`
  line `Securities and Exchange Board of India, if the Central Government is satisfied, that any person, who is`
  line `alleged to have violated any of the provisions of this Act or the rules or the regulations made thereunder,`
  line `has made a full and true disclosure in respect of alleged violation, grant to such person, subject to such`
  line `conditions as it may think fit to impose, immunity from prosecution for any offence under this Act, or the`
  line `rules or the regulations made thereunder or also from the imposition of any penalty under this Act with`
  line `respect to the alleged violation:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such immunity shall be granted by the Central Government in cases where the`
  line `proceedings for the prosecution for any such offence have been instituted before the date of receipt of`
  line `application for grant of such immunity:`
  line
  line `Provided futher that the recommendation of the Securities and Exchange Board of India under this`
  line `sub-section shall not be binding upon the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) An immunity granted to a person under sub-section (1) may, at any time, be withdrawn by the`
  line `Central Government, if it is satisfied that such person had, in the course of the proceedings, not complied`
  line `with the condition on which the immunity was granted or had given false evidence, and thereupon such`
  line `person may be tried for the offence with respect to which the immunity was granted or for any other`
  line `offence of which he appears to have been guilty in connection with the contravention and shall also`
  line `become liable to the imposition of any penalty under this Act to which such person would have been`
  line `liable, had not such immunity been granted.]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_o_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (14453)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 59
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14453&sectionno=24&orderno=59&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `24. ^1[Contravention by companies].--(1) Where ^2[a contravention of any of the provisions of this`
  line `Act or any rule, regulations, direction or order made thereunder] has been committed by a company,`
  line `every person who, at the time when the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was responsible to,`
  line `the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall be deemed to`
  line `be guilty of the offence, and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment provided in this Act, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or`
  line `that he exercised all due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where ^3[a contravention of any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act or any rule, regulation, direction or order made thereunder] has been committed by`
  line `a company and is proved that the ^4[contravention] has been committed with the consent or connivance of,`
  line `or is attributable to any gross negligence on the part of any director, manager, secretary or other officer of`
  line `the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer of the company, shall also be deemed to`
  line `be guilty of that ^4[offence] and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `^5[(3) The provisions of this section shall be in addition to and not in derogation of, the provisions of`
  line `section 22A.]`
  line
  line `Explanation .--For the purpose of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means any body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals,`
  line and
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(b) "director", in relation to--`
  line
  line `(i) a firm, means a partner in the firm;`
  line
  line `(ii) any association of persons or a body of individuals, means any member controlling the`
  line `affairs thereof.]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 159, ibid., for "Offences by companies" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 159, ibid., for "an offence" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 159, ibid., for "an offence under this Act" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 159, ibid., for "offence" (w.e.f. 8-3-2019).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 40 of 1985, s. 3 (w.e.f. 17-1-1986).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 7, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (14454)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 60
  title `Certain offences to be cognizable`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. The words, brackets and figure "sub-section (1) of" omitted by Act 1 of 2005, s. 12 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14454&sectionno=25&orderno=60&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5 of 1898), any offence punishable under ^1*** section 23 shall be deemed to`
  line `be cognizable offence within the meaning of that Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (14455)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 61
  title `Cognizance of offences by courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14455&sectionno=26&orderno=61&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `^1[26. Cognizance of offences by courts.--(1) No court shall take cognizance of any offence`
  line `punishable under this Act or any rules or regulations or bye-laws made thereunder, save on a complaint`
  line `made by the Central Government or State Government or the Securities and Exchange Board of India or a`
  line `recognised stock exchange or by any person.]`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for section 26 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line `2. Sub-section (2) omitted by Act 27 of 2014, s. 37 (w.e.f. 8-9-2014).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_a:
  sectionId (14456)
  sectionNo 26A
  orderNo 62
  title `Establishment of Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-9-2014)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14456&sectionno=26A&orderno=62&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_26_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[26A. Establishment of Special Courts.--(1) The Central Government may, for the purpose of`
  line `providing speedy trial of offences under this Act, by notification, establish or designate as many Special`
  line `Courts as may be necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) A Special Court shall consist of a single judge who shall be appointed by the Central Government`
  line `with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court within whose jurisdiction the judge to be`
  line `appointed is working.`
  line
  line `(3) A person shall not be qualified for appointment as a judge of a Special Court unless he is,`
  line `immediately before such appointment, holding the office of a Sessions Judge or an Additional Sessions`
  line `Judge, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_b:
  sectionId (14457)
  sectionNo 26B
  orderNo 63
  title `Offences triable by Special Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-9-2014)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14457&sectionno=26B&orderno=63&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_26_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[26B. Offences triable by Special Courts.--Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of`
  line `Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), all offences under this Act committed prior to the date of`
  line `commencement of the Securities Laws (Amendment) Act, 2014 (27 of 2014) or on or after the date of`
  line `such commencement, shall be taken cognizance of and tried by the Special Court established for the area`
  line `in which the offence is committed or where there are more Special Courts than one for such area, by such`
  line `one of them as may be specified in this behalf by the High Court concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_c:
  sectionId (14458)
  sectionNo 26C
  orderNo 64
  title `. Appeal and Revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-9-2014)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14458&sectionno=26C&orderno=64&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_26_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[26C. Appeal and Revision.--The High Court may exercise, so far as may be applicable, all the`
  line `powers conferred by Chapters XXIX and XXX of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) on a`
  line `High Court, as if a Special Court within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court were a Court`
  line `of Session trying cases within the local limits of the jurisdiction of the High Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_d:
  sectionId (14459)
  sectionNo 26D
  orderNo 65
  title `Application of Code to proceedings before Special Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-9-2014)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14459&sectionno=26D&orderno=65&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_26_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[26D. Application of Code to proceedings before Special Court.--(1) Save as otherwise provided`
  line `in this Act, the provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974) shall apply to the`
  line `proceedings before a Special Court and for the purposes of the said provisions, the Special Court shall be`
  line `deemed to be a Court of Session and the person conducting prosecution before a Special Court shall be`
  line `deemed to be a Public Prosecutor within the meaning of clause (u) of section 2 of the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973.`
  line
  line `(2) The person conducting prosecution referred to in sub-section (1) should have been in practice as`
  line `an advocate for not less than seven years or should have held a post, for a period of not less than seven`
  line `years, under the Union or a State, requiring special knowledge of law.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26_e:
  sectionId (14460)
  sectionNo 26E
  orderNo 66
  title `Transitional provisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 38, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-9-2014)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14460&sectionno=26E&orderno=66&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_26_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[26E. Transitional provisions.--Any offence committed under this Act, which is triable by a Special`
  line `Court shall, until a Special Court is established, be taken cognizance of and tried by a Court of Session`
  line `exercising jurisdiction over the area, notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal`
  line `Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974):`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this section shall affect the powers of the High Court under`
  line `section 407 of the Code to transfer any case or class of cases taken cognizance by a court of session under`
  line `this section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (14461)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 67
  title `Title to dividends.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14461&sectionno=27&orderno=67&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be lawful for the holder of any security whose name appears on`
  line `the books of the company issuing the said security to receive and retain any dividend declared by the`
  line `company in respect thereof for any year, notwithstanding that the said security has already been`
  line `transferred by him for consideration, unless the transferee who claims the dividend from the transferor has`
  line `lodged the security and all other documents relating to the transfer which may be required by the`
  line `company with the company for being registered in his name within fifteen days of the date on which the`
  line `dividend became due.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The period specified in this section shall be extended--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of death of the transferee, by the actual period taken by his legal representative to`
  line `establish his claim to the dividend;`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of loss of the transfer deed by theft or any other cause beyond the control of`
  line `the transferee, by the actual period taken for the replacement thereof; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in case of delay in the lodging of any security and other documents relating to the transfer`
  line `due to causes connected with the post, by the actual period of the delay.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall affect--`
  line
  line `(a) the right of a company to pay any dividend which has become due to any person whose`
  line `name is for the time being registered in the books of the company as the holder of the security in`
  line `respect of which the dividend has become due; or`
  line
  line `(b) the right of the transferee of any security to enforce against the transferor or any other`
  line `person his rights, if any, in relation to the transfer in any case where the company has refused to`
  line `register the transfer of the security in the name of the transferee.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (14462)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 68
  title `Right to receive income from collective investment scheme.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 8 (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14462&sectionno=27A&orderno=68&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[27A. Right to receive income from collective investment scheme.--(1) It shall be lawful for the`
  line `holder of any securities, being units or other instruments issued by the collective investment scheme,`
  line `whose name appears on the books of the collective investment scheme issuing the said security to receive`
  line `and retain any income in respect of units or other instruments issued by the collective investment scheme`
  line `declared by the collective investment scheme in respect thereof for any year, notwithstanding that the said`
  line `security, being units or other instruments issued by the collective investment scheme, has already been`
  line `transferred by him for consideration, unless the transferee who claims the income in respect of units or`
  line `other instruments issued by the collective investment scheme from the transfer or has lodged the security`
  line `and all other documents relating to the transfer which may be required by the collective investment`
  line `scheme with the collective investment scheme for being registered in his name within fifteen days of the`
  line `date on which the income in respect of units or other instruments issued by the collective investment`
  line `scheme became due.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The period specified in this section shall be extended--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of death of the transferee, by the actual period taken by his legal representative to`
  line `establish his claim to the income in respect of units or other instrument issued by the collective`
  line `investment scheme;`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of loss of the transfer deed by theft or any other cause beyond the control of the`
  line `transferee, by the actual period taken for the replacement thereof; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in case of delay in the lodging of any security, being units or other instruments issued by the`
  line `collective investment scheme, and other documents relating to the transfer due to causes connected`
  line `with the post, by the actual period of the delay.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall affect--`
  line
  line `(a) the right of a collective investment scheme to pay any income from units or other instruments`
  line `issued by the collective investment scheme which has become due to any person whose name is for the time being registered in the books of the collective investment scheme as the holder of the`
  line `security being units or other instruments issued by the collective investment scheme in respect of`
  line `which the income in respect of units or other instruments issued by the collective scheme has become`
  line `due; or`
  line
  line `(b) the right of transferee of any security, being units or other instruments issued by the collective`
  line `investment scheme, to enforce against the transferor or any other person his rights, if any, in relation`
  line `to the transfer in any case where the company has refused to register the transfer of the security being`
  line `units or other instruments issued by the collective investment scheme in the name of the transferee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_b:
  sectionId (14463)
  sectionNo 27B
  orderNo 69
  title `Right to receive income from mutual fund`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 14 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14463&sectionno=27B&orderno=69&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_27_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[27B. Right to receive income from mutual fund.--(1) It shall be lawful for the holder of any`
  line `securities, being units or other instruments issued by any mutual fund, whose name appears on the books`
  line `of the mutual fund issuing the said security to receive and retain any income in respect of units or other`
  line `instruments issued by the mutual fund declared by the mutual fund in respect thereof for any year,`
  line `notwithstanding that the said security, being units or other instruments issued by the mutual fund, has`
  line `already been transferred by him for consideration, unless the transferee who claims the income in respect`
  line `of units or other instruments issued by the mutual fund from the transferor has lodged the security and all`
  line `other documents relating to the transfer which may be required by the mutual fund with the mutual fund`
  line `for being registered in his name within fifteen days of the date on which the income in respect of units or`
  line `other instruments issued by the mutual fund became due.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The period specified in this section shall be extended--`
  line
  line `(i) in case of death of the transferee, by the actual period taken by his legal representative to`
  line `establish his claim to the income in respect of units or other instrument issued by the mutual fund;`
  line
  line `(ii) in case of loss of the transfer deed by theft or any other cause beyond the control of transferee,`
  line `by the actual period taken for the replacement thereof; and`
  line
  line `(iii) in case of delay in the lodging of any security, being units or other instruments issued by the`
  line `mutual fund, and other documents relating to the transfer due to causes connected with the post, by`
  line `the actual period of the delay.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing contained in sub-section (1) shall affect--`
  line
  line `(a) the right of a mutual fund to pay any income from units or other instruments issued by the`
  line `mutual fund which has become due to any person, whose name is for the time being registered in the`
  line `books of the mutual fund as the holder of the security being units or other instruments issued by the`
  line `mutual fund in respect of which the income in respect of units or other instruments issued by the`
  line `mutual fund has become due; or`
  line
  line `(b) the right of a transferee of any security, being units or other instruments issued by the mutual`
  line `fund, to enforce against the transferor or any other person, his rights, if any, in relation to the transfer`
  line `in any case where the mutual fund has refused to register the transfer of the security being units or`
  line `other instruments issued by the mutual fund in the name of the transferee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (14464)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 70
  title `Act not to apply in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 49 of 1959, s. 3, for section 28 (w.e.f. 8-12-1959).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14464&sectionno=28&orderno=70&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `^1[28. Act not to apply in certain cases.--(1) The provisions of this Act shall not apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the Government, the Reserve Bank of India, any local authority or any corporation set up by a`
  line `special law or any person who has effected any transaction with or through the agency of any such`
  line `authority as is referred to in this clause;`
  line
  line `(b) any convertible bond or share warrant or any option or right in relation thereto, in so far as it`
  line `entitles the person in whose favour any of the foregoing has been issued to obtain at his option from`
  line `the company or other body corporate issuing the same or from any of its shareholders or duly`
  line `appointed agents shares of the company or other body corporate, whether by conversion of the bond`
  line `or warrant or otherwise, on the basis of the price agreed upon when the same was issued.`
  line
  line `(2) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1), if the Central Government is`
  line `satisfied that in the interests of trade and commerce or the economic development of the country it is`
  line `necessary or expedient so to do, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify any class of`
  line `contracts as contracts to which this Act or any provision contained therein shall not apply, and also the`
  line `conditions, limitations or restrictions, if any, subject to which it shall not so apply.]`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (14465)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 71
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14465&sectionno=29&orderno=71&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `whatsoever shall lie in any court against the governing body or any member, office bearer or servant of`
  line `any recognised stock exchange or against any person or persons appointed under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 11 for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or of`
  line `any rules or bye-laws made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29_a:
  sectionId (14466)
  sectionNo 29A
  orderNo 72
  title `power to delegate`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 9, for section 29A (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14466&sectionno=29A&orderno=72&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_29_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[29A. power to delegate.--The Central Government may, by order published in the Official`
  line `Gazette, direct that the powers (except the power under section 30) exercisable by it under any provision`
  line `of this Act shall, in relation to such matters and subject to such conditions, if any, as may be specified in`
  line `the order, be exercisable also by the Securities and Exchange Board of India or the Reserve Bank of India`
  line `constituted under section 3 of the Reserve Bank of India Act, 1934 (2 of 1934).]`
obj_root_law_sections_29_b:
  sectionId (50609)
  sectionNo 29B
  orderNo 73
  title `Powers of the Securities and Exchange Board of India not to apply to International Financial Services Centre.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 50 of 2019, s. 33 and the second Schedule (w.e.f. 1-10-2020).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=50609&sectionno=29B&orderno=73&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_29_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[29B. Powers of the Securities and Exchange Board of India not to apply to International`
  line `Financial Services Centre.--Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line `force, the powers exercisable by the Securities and Exchange Board of India under this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) shall not extend to an International Financial Services Centre set up under sub-section (1)`
  line `of section18 of the Special Economic Zones Act, 2005 (28 of 2005);`
  line
  line `(b) shall be exercisable by the International Financial Services Centres Authority established`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 4 of the International Financial Services Centres Authority Act,`
  line 2019,
  line
  line `in so far as regulation of financial products, financial services and financial institutions that are permitted`
  line `in the International Financial Services Centres are concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (14467)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 74
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14467&sectionno=30&orderno=74&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for the purpose of carrying into effect the objects of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for,--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner in which applications may be made, the particulars which they should contain and`
  line `the levy of a fee in respect of such applications;`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which any inquiry for the purpose of recognising any stock exchange may be`
  line `made, the conditions which may be imposed for the grant of such recognition, including conditions as`
  line `to the admission of members if the stock exchange concerned is to be the only recognised stock`
  line `exchange in the area; and the form in which such recognition shall be granted;`
  line
  line `(c) the particulars which should be contained in the periodical returns and annual reports to be`
  line `furnished to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(d) the documents which should be maintained and preserved under section 6 and the periods for`
  line `which they should be preserved;`
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which any inquiry by the governing body of a stock exchange shall be made`
  line `under section 6;`
  line
  line `(f) the manner in which the bye-laws to be made or amended under this Act shall before being so`
  line `made or amended be published for criticism;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner in which applications may be made by dealers in securities for licences under`
  line `section 17, the fee payable in respect thereof and the period of such licences, the conditions subject to`
  line `which licences may be granted, including conditions relating to the forms which may be used in`
  line `making contracts, the documents to be maintained by licensed dealers and the furnishing of periodical`
  line `information to such authority as may be specified and the revocation of licences for breach of`
  line conditions;
  line
  line `^1[(h) the requirements which shall be complied with--`
  line
  line `(A) by public companies for the purpose of getting their securities listed on any stock`
  line exchange;
  line
  line `(B) by collective investment scheme for the purpose of getting their units listed on any stock`
  line exchange.]
  line
  line `^2[(ha) the grounds on which the securities of a company may be delisted from any recognised`
  line `stock exchange under sub-section (1) of section 21A;`
  line
  line `(hb) the form in which an appeal may be filed before the Securities Appellate Tribunal under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 21A and the fees payable in respect of such appeal;`
  line
  line `(hc) the form in which an appeal may be filed before the Securities Appellate Tribunal under`
  line `section 22A and the fees payable in respect of such appeal;`
  line
  line `(hd) the manner of inquiry under sub-section (1) of section 23-I;`
  line
  line `(he) the form in which an appeal may be filed before the Securities Appellate Tribunal under`
  line `section 23L and the fees payable in respect of such appeal;]`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which is to be or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^3[(3) Every rule made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 31 of 1999, s. 10, ibid, for clause (h) (w.e.f. 22-2-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 15, for clause (ha) (w.e.f.12-10-2004).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_30_a:
  sectionId (14468)
  sectionNo 30A
  orderNo 75
  title `Special provisions related to commodity derivatives.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 20 of 2015, s. 135 (w.e.f. 14-5-2015).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14468&sectionno=30A&orderno=75&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_30_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[30A. Special provisions related to commodity derivatives.--(1) Nothing contained in this Act`
  line `shall apply to non-transferable specific delivery contracts:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall organise or assist in organising or be a member of any association in`
  line `any area to which the provisions of section 13 have been made applicable (other than a stock exchange)`
  line `which provides facilities for the performance of any non-transferable specific delivery contract by any`
  line `party thereto without having to make or receive actual delivery to or from the other party to the contract`
  line `or to or from any other party named in the contract.`
  line
  line `(2) Where in respect of any area, the provisions of section 13 have been made applicable in relation to`
  line `commodity derivatives for the sale or purchase of any goods or class of goods, the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification, declare that in the said area or any part thereof as may be specified in the`
  line `notification all or any of the provisions of this Act shall not apply to transferable specific delivery`
  line `contracts for the sale or purchase of the said goods or class of goods either generally, or to any class of`
  line `such contracts in particular.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), if the Central Government is of the`
  line `opinion that in the interest of the trade or in the public interest it is expedient to regulate and control nontransferable`
  line `specific delivery contracts in any area, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare`
  line `that all or any of the provisions of this Act shall apply to such class or classes of non-transferable specific`
  line `delivery contracts in such area in respect of such goods or class of goods as may be specified in the`
  line `notification, and may also specify the manner in which and the extent to which all or any of the said`
  line `provisions shall so apply.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30_b:
  sectionId (56391)
  sectionNo 30B
  orderNo 76
  title `Special provisions related to pooled investment vehicle.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 13 of 2021, s. 149 (w.e.f. 1-4-2021).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=56391&sectionno=30B&orderno=76&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_30_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[30B. Special provisions related to pooled investment vehicle.—(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Indian Trust Act, 1882 (2 of 1882) or in any other law for the time being in force or in`
  line `any judgment, decree or order of any Court, Tribunal or any other authority, a pooled investment vehicle,`
  line `whether constituted as a trust or otherwise, and registered with the Securities and Exchange Board of`
  line `India shall be eligible to borrow and issue debt securities in such manner and to such extent as may be`
  line `specified under the regulations made by Securities and Exchange Board of India in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Every pooled investment vehicle referred to in sub-section (1) shall, subject to the provisions of`
  line `the trust deed, be permitted to provide security interest to lenders in terms of the facility documents`
  line `entered into by such pooled investment vehicle.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any pooled investment vehicle referred to in sub-section (1) defaults in repayment of`
  line `principal amount or payment of interest or any such amount due to the lender, the lender shall recover the`
  line `defaulted amount and enforce security interest, if any, against the trust assets, by initiating proceedings`
  line `against the trustee acting on behalf of such pooled investment vehicle in accordance with the terms and`
  line `conditions specified in the facility documents:`
  line
  line `Provided that on initiation of the proceedings against the trust assets, the trustee shall not be`
  line `personally liable and his assets shall not be utilised towards recovery of such debt.`
  line
  line `(4) The trust assets, which remain after recovery of defaulted amount, shall be remitted to the unit`
  line `holders on proportionate basis.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (14469)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 77
  title `Power of Securities and Exchange Board of India to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14469&sectionno=31&orderno=77&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[31. Power of Securities and Exchange Board of India to make regulations.--(1) Without`
  line `prejudice to the provisions contained in section 30 of the Securities and Exchange Board of India Act,`
  line `1992 (15 of 1992), the Securities and Exchange Board of India may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, make regulations consistent with the provisions of this Act and the rules made thereunder to`
  line `carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the manner, in which at least fifty-one per cent. of equity share capital of a recognised stock`
  line `exchange is held within twelve months from the date of publication of the order under sub-section (7)`
  line `of section 4B by the public other than the shareholders having trading rights under sub-section (8) of`
  line `that section;`
  line
  line `(b) the eligibility criteria and other requirements under section 17A.`
  line
  line `^3[(c) the terms determined by the Board for settlement of proceedings under sub-section (2) of`
  line `section 23JA;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, specified by regulations or in respect of`
  line `which provision is to be made by regulations.]`
  line
  line `(3) Every regulation made under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one`
  line `session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made, the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 2005, s. 16 (w.e.f. 12-10-2004).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 27 of 2007, s. 5, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 28-5-2007).`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 27 of 2014, s. 39 (w.e.f. 8-9-2014)`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (14470)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 78
  title `Validation of certain acts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 40, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-9-2014)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094&sectionId=14470&sectionno=32&orderno=78&orgactid=AC_CEN_2_11_00019_195642_1517807321094
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `^1[32. Validation of certain acts.--Any act or thing done or purporting to have been done under the`
  line `principal Act, in respect of settlement of administrative and civil proceedings, shall, for all purposes, be`
  line `deemed to be valid and effective as if the amendments made to the principal Act had been in force at all`
  line `material times.]`
